value: an astronomer wearing a himation, left arm and shoulder bare, sitting on the ground beneath a tree, in profile to the left.  He is measuring a globe with compasses held in his right hand; the sun, the moon and five stars above him, formerly picked out with pyretic inclusions.  Mount: gold ring, type 1a.

summary_title: Classical Gems, Ancient and Modern Intaglios and Cameos in the Fitzwilliam Museum, Cambridge
